<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=238408"> What I wear to kill stuff. </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=neydini>Neydini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/28/02 11:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> This spell far too unbalancing..esp in PvP</span><hr size=1> Pre-PoP, an epic Mage was probably the most efficient PvP killing class in game.  About the only chance a Wizard had to kill said mage was to MB him (which, BTW still holds true for the majority of the classes).  <br>
<br>
First of all, I would like to make it clear I am not asking for a nerf --  I am just asking for relative balance..meaning the advantage of one class to another is situational.  When one class has the advantage 99% of the time, that to me is not balance, and something could be done to rectify this.  In PvE, this is unbalancing, as an epic mage could feasibly outdamage a similiarly equipped Wizard 95% of the time.  Those of you taht say EER and GSR are obtainable need to get out more..that claim is absurd.  (1 COPY of GSR on my server to date)<br>
<br>
There was much clamour about the MB skill being overpowered in PvP.  I have not, however, seen much discussion as to how much of an improvement this spell is to an already powerful PvP class.<br>
<br>
Have you ventured to the arena lately ?  Try dancing with a Epic Mage/2000 bolt enabled mage for 10 seconds..Sure, you MAY get a MB off for one kill..then youd be facing 2 hours 20 minutes worth of pure pounding, and I would venture you would be lucky to get 1 spell off the rest of the evening...so, you are advantaged when MB is up (which, over a 3 hour period is ONCE) and the rest of the advantage is to the mage..balance ?<br>
<br>
Consider this as well..when PvP'ing against an epic mage, it is vital to deal with the &gt; sow speed Pet that is dualing you for 60 a round, as well as stunning you first..all while getting bolted for 1700 or so non-crit ?  How do you do this effectively ? One bolt, I am nearly dead..this is MB with insta refresh..wow..this is just wrong.  <br>
<br>
This spell should be as rare as GSR. and a level 64-65 spell.  This would keep in line with the current spell drop/power per level/class.  <br>
<br>
I wonder if this isn't a bone thrown to the mAges for the God Rod II nerf..hrmm..didnt we also recieve a MB nerf flogging ?  Where is our bone ? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=belarkan>Belarkan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 168<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/29/02 7:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> This spell far too unbalancing..esp in PvP</span><hr size=1> Thats weird, my experience with Epic magicians in PvP is very different, i win about 2/3 of the times, either root the pet and own his master, either just stand still in a corner and chain cast Lure of Ice while pet eat our rune, and while magi nukes get resisted/ absorbed by BoF/SS.<br>
<br>
It isnt very fair this bolt is vendor sold only, but in PvP situation im sure Lure of Thunder is worth much more.<br>
